<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Slice on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/slice/</link><description>Recent content in Slice on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/slice/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Go Index Out of Range — Runtime Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/index-out-of-range-2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/index-out-of-range-2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="index-out-of-range--runtime-error-fix"&gt;Index Out of Range — Runtime Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An index out of range panic occurs when you try to access a slice, array, or string at a position that doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Go performs bounds checking on slice, array, and string access. If the index is negative or greater than or equal to the length, the runtime panics with &lt;code&gt;runtime error: index out of range [N] with length M&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common scenarios:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Go Index Out of Range — Runtime Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/index-out-of-range/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/index-out-of-range/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="index-out-of-range--runtime-error"&gt;Index Out of Range — Runtime Error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The error &lt;code&gt;runtime error: index out of range&lt;/code&gt; occurs when you access a slice or array element using an index that is negative or greater than or equal to the length of the collection.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Go slices and arrays are zero-indexed. An index of &lt;code&gt;len(s)&lt;/code&gt; or higher is out of bounds. Negative indices also cause this panic. Unlike languages with automatic bounds checking that return sentinel values, Go terminates the program immediately.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Go Slice Bounds Out of Range — Runtime Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/slice-bounds-out-of-range-2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/slice-bounds-out-of-range-2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="slice-bounds-out-of-range--runtime-error-fix"&gt;Slice Bounds Out of Range — Runtime Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A slice bounds out of range panic occurs when a slice expression uses indices that are outside the valid range of the underlying array or slice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Go slices have a length and capacity. Slice expressions &lt;code&gt;s[low:high]&lt;/code&gt; require that &lt;code&gt;0 &amp;lt;= low &amp;lt;= high &amp;lt;= cap(s)&lt;/code&gt;. Violating any of these constraints panics with &lt;code&gt;runtime error: slice bounds out of range [N] with length M&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Go Slice Bounds Out of Range — Runtime Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/slice-bounds-out-of-range/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/slice-bounds-out-of-range/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="slice-bounds-out-of-range--runtime-error-fix"&gt;Slice Bounds Out of Range — Runtime Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A slice bounds out of range panic occurs when a slice expression uses bounds that exceed the slice&amp;rsquo;s length or capacity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In Go, slice expressions &lt;code&gt;s[low:high]&lt;/code&gt; require &lt;code&gt;0 &amp;lt;= low &amp;lt;= high &amp;lt;= cap(s)&lt;/code&gt;. If &lt;code&gt;high&lt;/code&gt; exceeds the capacity or &lt;code&gt;low&lt;/code&gt; exceeds &lt;code&gt;high&lt;/code&gt;, the runtime panics with &lt;code&gt;runtime error: slice bounds out of range&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common scenarios:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Slicing beyond capacity&lt;/strong&gt; — &lt;code&gt;s[:100]&lt;/code&gt; when &lt;code&gt;cap(s)&lt;/code&gt; is 50.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Slicing with reversed bounds&lt;/strong&gt; — &lt;code&gt;s[5:2]&lt;/code&gt; where low &amp;gt; high.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Slicing a nil slice&lt;/strong&gt; — &lt;code&gt;var s []int; s[0:5]&lt;/code&gt; panics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Using &lt;code&gt;append&lt;/code&gt; result without checking&lt;/strong&gt; — &lt;code&gt;append&lt;/code&gt; may return a new slice with different capacity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-go" data-lang="go"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Slicing beyond capacity&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt; make([]&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;sub&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt;[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;] &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// panic: slice bounds out of range [2:10] with capacity 5&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Reversed bounds&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt; []&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;{&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;sub&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt;[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;] &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// panic: slice bounds out of range [2:1]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Nil slice slicing&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt; []&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;sub&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt;[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;] &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// panic: slice bounds out of range [0:5] with length 0&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 4: Slicing after append that grows the backing array&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt; make([]&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;4&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt; = append(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;4&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// capacity used up&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Original capacity reference is stale&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;sub&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt;[:&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;] &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// panic&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-check-capacity-before-slicing-beyond-length"&gt;Fix 1: Check capacity before slicing beyond length&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-go" data-lang="go"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;sub&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt;[:&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt;]
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Correct&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; cap(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;sub&lt;/span&gt; = &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt;[:&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt;]
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;} &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;sub&lt;/span&gt; = &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt;[:cap(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt;)]
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-ensure-low--high-in-slice-expressions"&gt;Fix 2: Ensure low &amp;lt;= high in slice expressions&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-go" data-lang="go"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;func&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;sliceRange&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt; []&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;low&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;high&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;) []&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt;[&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;low&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;high&lt;/span&gt;]
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Correct&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;func&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;sliceRange&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt; []&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;low&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;high&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;) []&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;low&lt;/span&gt; &amp;lt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;||&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;high&lt;/span&gt; &amp;lt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;low&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;||&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;high&lt;/span&gt; &amp;gt; len(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;nil&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt;[&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;low&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;high&lt;/span&gt;]
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-initialize-slices-before-slicing"&gt;Fix 3: Initialize slices before slicing&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-go" data-lang="go"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt; []&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;sub&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt;[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;]
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Correct&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt; make([]&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;sub&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt;[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;]
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-4-use-the-three-index-slice-to-limit-capacity"&gt;Fix 4: Use the three-index slice to limit capacity&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-go" data-lang="go"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong — may accidentally share backing array&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;sub&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt;[:len(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt;)]
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Correct — explicitly control capacity&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;sub&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt;[:len(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt;):len(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt;)]
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-5-check-length-before-slicing"&gt;Fix 5: Check length before slicing&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-go" data-lang="go"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;func&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;firstN&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt; []&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;) []&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt;[:&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;] &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// panics if n &amp;gt; len(s)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Correct&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;func&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;firstN&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt; []&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;) []&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &amp;gt; len(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; = len(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt;[:&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;]
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-go" data-lang="go"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// This triggers: runtime error: slice bounds out of range [5:3] with length 4&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;package&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;fmt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;func&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt; []&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;{&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;4&lt;/span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;fmt&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Println&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt;[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;])
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/index-out-of-range/"&gt;index-out-of-range&lt;/a&gt; — accessing a single index beyond the slice length.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/nil-pointer/"&gt;nil-pointer&lt;/a&gt; — dereferencing a nil pointer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/out-of-memory/"&gt;out-of-memory&lt;/a&gt; — allocating too much memory with large slices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Go Slice Bounds Out of Range — Runtime Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/slice-bounds/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/slice-bounds/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="slice-bounds-out-of-range--runtime-error"&gt;Slice Bounds Out of Range — Runtime Error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The error &lt;code&gt;runtime error: slice bounds out of range&lt;/code&gt; occurs when you use a slice expression (&lt;code&gt;s[low:high]&lt;/code&gt;) where &lt;code&gt;low&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;high&lt;/code&gt; exceeds the slice&amp;rsquo;s length or capacity, or where &lt;code&gt;low &amp;gt; high&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When reslicing in Go, the bounds must satisfy: &lt;code&gt;0 &amp;lt;= low &amp;lt;= high &amp;lt;= cap(s)&lt;/code&gt;. If &lt;code&gt;high&lt;/code&gt; exceeds the capacity or &lt;code&gt;low&lt;/code&gt; is greater than &lt;code&gt;high&lt;/code&gt;, Go panics at runtime. This differs from index-out-of-range errors because it involves slice expressions rather than single-element access.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Python ValueError — Slice Length Must Be Positive</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/wrong-slice-length/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/wrong-slice-length/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="valueerror--slice-length-must-be-positive"&gt;ValueError — Slice Length Must Be Positive&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;ValueError&lt;/code&gt; with the message &amp;ldquo;slice length must be positive&amp;rdquo; is raised when you try to create a slice with a negative or zero length. This typically occurs when the start index is greater than the stop index with a positive step, or when using &lt;code&gt;range()&lt;/code&gt; with invalid arguments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Slicing in Python follows specific rules. When using a positive step, the start index must be less than the stop index. When using a negative step, the start index must be greater than the stop index. Violating these rules results in an empty slice, but certain operations that require positive length will raise this error.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Python ValueError — Slice Step Cannot Be Zero</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/slice-step-zero/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/slice-step-zero/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="valueerror--slice-step-cannot-be-zero"&gt;ValueError — Slice Step Cannot Be Zero&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;ValueError&lt;/code&gt; with the message &amp;ldquo;slice step cannot be zero&amp;rdquo; is raised when you use &lt;code&gt;0&lt;/code&gt; as the step in a slice operation like &lt;code&gt;list[start:stop:0]&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;range(0)&lt;/code&gt;. The step parameter determines how many elements to skip, and skipping zero elements creates an infinite loop.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Slicing in Python uses the syntax &lt;code&gt;sequence[start:stop:step]&lt;/code&gt;. The &lt;code&gt;step&lt;/code&gt; parameter controls the increment between elements. A step of 0 would mean &amp;ldquo;take the same element forever,&amp;rdquo; which is undefined behavior. Valid steps are positive (forward) or negative (backward).&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Rust Index Out of Bounds — Vec Index Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/index-out-of-bounds/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/index-out-of-bounds/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="index-out-of-bounds--vec-index-error"&gt;Index Out of Bounds — Vec Index Error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A panic with the message &amp;ldquo;index out of bounds: the len is X but the index is Y&amp;rdquo; occurs when you attempt to access an element at an index that is greater than or equal to the length of the collection.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rust collections like &lt;code&gt;Vec&lt;/code&gt;, arrays, and slices use zero-based indexing. A collection of length &lt;code&gt;n&lt;/code&gt; has valid indices from &lt;code&gt;0&lt;/code&gt; to &lt;code&gt;n-1&lt;/code&gt;. Indexing outside this range causes a runtime panic. This is a deliberate safety check — Rust prevents out-of-bounds memory access, which would be undefined behavior in C/C++.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Rust Index Out of Bounds — Vec Length Exceeded</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/index-out-of-bounds-2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/index-out-of-bounds-2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="index-out-of-bounds--vec-length-exceeded"&gt;Index Out of Bounds — Vec Length Exceeded&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A panic with the message &amp;ldquo;index out of bounds: the len is X but the index is Y&amp;rdquo; occurs when you access an element at an index that exceeds the collection&amp;rsquo;s length.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rust prevents undefined behavior by bounds-checking every array, Vec, and slice access. If the index Y is greater than or equal to the length X, the runtime panics immediately. This catch prevents memory corruption that would occur in unchecked languages.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Rust Index Out of Bounds Panic — Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/bounds-panic/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/bounds-panic/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="index-out-of-bounds-panic"&gt;Index Out of Bounds Panic&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The error &lt;code&gt;index out of bounds: the len is X but the index is Y&lt;/code&gt; occurs when you use the &lt;code&gt;[]&lt;/code&gt; operator with an index that exceeds the collection&amp;rsquo;s length. This is a runtime panic, not a compile-time error.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rust&amp;rsquo;s indexing operator (&lt;code&gt;[]&lt;/code&gt;) performs bounds checking at runtime. When the index is outside the valid range (0 to len-1), the program panics. Unlike some languages that return a default value or sentinel, Rust terminates the thread.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Rust Slice Index Out of Bounds — Range Exceeds Length</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/slice-index-2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/slice-index-2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="slice-index-out-of-bounds--range-exceeds-length"&gt;Slice Index Out of Bounds — Range Exceeds Length&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A panic with the message &amp;ldquo;index out of bounds: the len is X but the index is Y&amp;rdquo; occurs when you create a slice using a range whose end index exceeds the collection&amp;rsquo;s length.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Slicing in Rust uses range syntax like &lt;code&gt;&amp;amp;vec[start..end]&lt;/code&gt;. The end index must be less than or equal to the collection length, and the start must be less than or equal to the end. When a range extends past the end of the data, the runtime panics with the length and the offending index.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Rust Slice Index Out of Bounds — Slice Length Mismatch</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/slice-index/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/slice-index/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="slice-index-out-of-bounds--slice-length-mismatch"&gt;Slice Index Out of Bounds — Slice Length Mismatch&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A panic with the message &amp;ldquo;index out of bounds: the len is X but the index is Y&amp;rdquo; occurs when you create a slice with a range that extends beyond the collection&amp;rsquo;s bounds.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Slicing in Rust uses range syntax like &lt;code&gt;&amp;amp;vec[start..end]&lt;/code&gt;. Both &lt;code&gt;start&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;end&lt;/code&gt; must be within the bounds of the collection, and &lt;code&gt;start&lt;/code&gt; must be less than or equal to &lt;code&gt;end&lt;/code&gt;. Violating these constraints causes a runtime panic. This commonly happens when calculating slice ranges dynamically.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Systemd Slice Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/systemd/slice-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/systemd/slice-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="systemd-slice-error"&gt;Systemd Slice Error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A slice error occurs when a systemd unit cannot be placed in its specified cgroup slice, or the slice itself has invalid configuration. Slices control resource limits (CPU, memory, I/O) for groups of services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The slice unit file is missing or has syntax errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The referenced slice does not exist&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Memory or CPU limits in the slice exceed system capabilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The slice hierarchy is too deep (exceeds cgroup depth limits)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="verify-the-slice-exists"&gt;Verify the Slice Exists&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;systemctl status my-app.slice
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;systemctl list-units --type&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;slice
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="create-a-custom-slice"&gt;Create a Custom Slice&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ini" data-lang="ini"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# /etc/systemd/system/my-app.slice&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;[Unit]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Description&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;Slice for My Application&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;[Slice]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;MemoryMax&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;2G&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;CPUQuota&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;150%&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;TasksMax&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;512&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="assign-a-service-to-the-slice"&gt;Assign a Service to the Slice&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ini" data-lang="ini"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# /etc/systemd/system/my-app.service&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;[Unit]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Description&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;My Application&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;[Service]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Slice&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;my-app.slice&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;ExecStart&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;/usr/bin/my-app&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="reload-and-restart"&gt;Reload and Restart&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo systemctl daemon-reload
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo systemctl restart my-app
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="check-slice-resource-usage"&gt;Check Slice Resource Usage&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;systemctl status my-app.slice
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;systemd-cgtop
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Missing slice referenced by service&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# my-app.service: Failed with result &amp;#39;dependency&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Fix: create my-app.slice or remove Slice= directive&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Memory limit too high for available resources&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# my-app.slice: Failed to set memory limit&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Fix: reduce MemoryMax to a feasible value&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/systemd/failed-dependency/"&gt;Failed Dependency&lt;/a&gt; — dependency chain failure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/systemd/permission-error7/"&gt;Permission Error&lt;/a&gt; — insufficient capabilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] JavaScript String.substr() Deprecated — Use slice() Instead</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/deprecated/javascript/substr-to-slice/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/deprecated/javascript/substr-to-slice/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-javascript-stringsubstr-deprecated--use-slice-instead"&gt;[Solution] JavaScript String.substr() Deprecated — Use slice() Instead&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;String.prototype.substr()&lt;/code&gt; method was deprecated in the ES2015 (ES6) specification. While it is still available in most JavaScript engines for backward compatibility, it should not be used in new code. The recommended replacement is &lt;code&gt;slice()&lt;/code&gt;, which is consistent with &lt;code&gt;Array.prototype.slice()&lt;/code&gt; and handles edge cases more predictably. For some use cases, &lt;code&gt;substring()&lt;/code&gt; is also appropriate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-youll-see"&gt;What You&amp;rsquo;ll See&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Using &lt;code&gt;substr()&lt;/code&gt; will not immediately break your code, but linters and static analysis tools will flag it:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>